{"key":"processedPost-11452650","value":{"id":11452650,"first":11450218,"last":11452820,"when":1258214037,"utime":"11/14/09 05:53 PM","cleanedPost":"You really need a flowhood for doing jar to bag transfers if you want any degree of success. For best results, you want a plenum of air in the bag above the grains, and without a flowhood, it's hard to fill up the bag with clean air. You also don't need an impulse sealer.&nbsp; I make up several hundred large gusseted bags of rye berries per month and don't own an impulse sealer.&nbsp; I prefer to tie the bags shut with wire.&nbsp; The large, gusseted spawn bags will hold 7 quarts at about 60% full.<br />RR"}}